 (see above — do this every time, no exceptions)."}]}]},{"type":"list_item","attrs":{"isCollapsed":false},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"strong"}],"text":"Identify the source type"},{"type":"text","text":": video transcript, journal article, presentation/slides, clinical guideline, highlights file, or general prose."}]}]},{"type":"list_item","attrs":{"isCollapsed":false},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"strong"}],"text":"Identify the topic type"},{"type":"text","text":": disease/condition, procedure/technique, drug/agent, or emergency/acute presentation."}]}]},{"type":"list_item","attrs":{"isCollapsed":false},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"strong"}],"text":"Extract the clinical bottom line"},{"type":"text","text":" — what does the anaesthetist need to know and do?"}]}]},{"type":"list_item","attrs":{"isCollapsed":false},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"strong"}],"text":"Handle embedded images"},{"type":"text","text":" — if the source contains image or figure references ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code_inline"}],"text":"![[...]]"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code_inline"}],"text":"![](path)"},{"type":"text","text":"), read each image using the Read tool, understand what it depicts, and plan where it belongs in the output. Do not silently drop figures."}]}]},{"type":"list_item","attrs":{"isCollapsed":false},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"strong"}],"text":"Transform"},{"type":"text","text":" the content following the rules in the style guide (Section 5: Content Transformation Rules)."}]}]},{"type":"list_item","attrs":{"isCollapsed":false},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"strong"}],"text":"Structure"},{"type":"text","text":" using the appropriate OHA template for the topic type (Section 2.2 of the style guide). Embed figures at the contextually appropriate location with a brief italicised caption (e.g. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code_inline"}],"text":"*Fig. 1 — FA/FI curves for common volatile agents*"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]}]},{"type":"list_item","attrs":{"isCollapsed":false},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"strong"}],"text":"Apply formatting"},{"type":"text","text":" — symbols, abbreviations, bullet conventions, units (Sections 3–4 of the style guide)."}]}]},{"type":"list_item","attrs":{"isCollapsed":false},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"strong"}],"text":"Run the quality checklist"},{"type":"text","text":" (Section 9 of the style guide) before presenting the output."}]}]},{"type":"list_item","attrs":{"isCollapsed":false},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"strong"}],"text":"Output"},{"type":"text","text":" — ask the user whether they want the notes saved to a file or displayed inline in the conversation, then deliver accordingly. If context makes the preference obvious (e.g. the user specified a destination path, or said \"show me\"), skip asking and proceed."}]}]}]}},"version":2,"versionNonce":413265304,"index":"aQ","isDeleted":false,"roughness":1,"seed":1,"groupIds":[],"frameId":null,"updated":1777041056534,"locked":false},{"id":"299q3zn45068l0w6j5ls33","type":"text","x":2608.6,"y":2465,"width":277.20000000000005,"height":70,"angle":0,"strokeColor":"#E65100","backgroundColor":"transparent","fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":2,"strokeStyle":"solid","opacity":100,"roundness":null,"originalText":"[ordered_list]","text":"[ordered_\nlist]","fontSize":28,"fontFamily":5,"textAlign":"center","verticalAlign":"middle","containerId":"pstkxl18zgjgkydkxd538s","autoResize":true,"lineHeight":1.25,"lineCount":2,"version":2,"versionNonce":753883112,"index":"aR","isDeleted":false,"roughness":1,"seed":1,"groupIds