":{"isCollapsed":false},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"strong"}],"text":"Presentations/slides"},{"type":"text","text":": Slide titles often map to subheadings. Tighten existing bullet points further. Use speaker notes for nuance if available."}]}]},{"type":"list_item","attrs":{"isCollapsed":false},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"strong"}],"text":"Highlights files (Obsidian)"},{"type":"text","text":": Source will contain a mix of quoted textbook passages, user annotations, and embedded image references. Treat user annotations as primary — they reflect the user's own understanding and should be incorporated faithfully. For each image reference ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code_inline"}],"text":"![](path)"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code_inline"}],"text":"![[...]]"},{"type":"text","text":"), read the image, identify what it shows (graph, diagram, table, figure), and embed it in the output at the point where the surrounding text calls for it. Adjust the image path to be correct relative to the output file's location. Add a brief italicised caption beneath each image describing what it depicts."}]}]}]}},"version":2,"versionNonce":1109103512,"index":"b0O","isDeleted":false,"roughness":1,"seed":1,"groupIds":[],"frameId":null,"updated":1777041056535,"locked":false},{"id":"juty510r6gf4nibf1m2p7y","type":"text","x":3666.6,"y":8207.5,"width":286,"height":25,"angle":0,"strokeColor":"#4A148C","backgroundColor":"transparent","fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":2,"strokeStyle":"solid","opacity":100,"roundness":null,"originalText":"[bullet_list]","text":"[bullet_list]","fontSize":20,"fontFamily":5,"textAlign":"center","verticalAlign":"middle","containerId":"gyc8oe1qtknpsq9u9r67","autoResize":true,"lineHeight":1.25,"lineCount":1,"version":2,"versionNonce":768283112,"index":"b0P","isDeleted":false,"roughness":1,"seed":1,"groupIds":[],"frameId":null,"boundE